For Ubuntu:

Install nodejs:
sudo apt update;
sudo apt install nodejs;

Install npm:
sudo apt install npm;

For Windows:

Install nodejs with npm:
1. Go to the site https://nodejs.org/en/download/ and download the necessary binary files.
2. Double click on the downloaded .msi file to start the installation. Click the Run button.
3. Click the "Next" button to continue with the installation.

Open command line and create a directory:
for example: mkdir test-task

Unzip arhiv to folder 'test-task'.

Change directory with command line:
for example: cd test-task

Install node module
npm install prompt-list

Run programm with command line:
node task.js

Select output mode.
